<HEADLINE>
OPTOELECTRONICS COMPANY TO PROVIDE 5,500 NEW JOBS IN SOUTHERN
TAIWAN
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan.  9 (CNA) 01/10/07  11:31:01 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
An official of Chi Mei Opetoectronics Corp. announced Tuesday
that the company's new assembly lines at the Southern Taiwan
Science Park in Tainan will provide between 5,000 and 5,500 jobs.
</P>
<P>
Lu Kuan-pan deputy director of Chi Mei's administrative office,
told a press conference that 1,500 of the jobs will be for
engineers, while the rest will be for assembly line workers. He
said the company will begin to recruit in Kaohsiung from Jan. 20.
</P>
<P>
Optoelectronics is a field of technology that combines the
physics  of light with electricity.  Its technologies  include
fiberoptic communications, laser systems, electric eyes, remote
sensing systems, medical diagnostic systems and optical
information systems.
</P>
<P>
Executives from the 1111 Manpower Bank, an online job search
firm, told the press conference that the launch of the Taiwan
High Speed Railway is expected to expand Taiwan's job market by
providing easier accessibility to job seekers and that the rise
of the Southern Taiwan Science Park could put the job market in
southern Taiwan on a par with that of northern Taiwan.
</P>
